text: , sometimes called Matsuzaka, is a city in central Mie Prefecture. It is on the island of Honshū, Japan. The city is famous for its Matsusaka beef. ==Famous people== *Mitsui Takatoshi (三井高利) (1622–1694) - founder of the Mitsui group. *Motoori Norinaga (本居宣長) (1730–1801) - scholar of the Edo period whose teachings were based on the kokugaku, the rejection all foreign, particularly Chinese, influence on Japanese culture. *Kana Nishino (西野カナ) (1989-) - J-pop/R&B; singer ==Other websites== * Category:Cities in Mie Prefecture
